Upgrade Rules
When upgrading an existing item:

Never change core_id - it must match the item you're upgrading
Set upgrades_previous to the same core_id you're upgrading
Try to keep but enhance the physical item core, don't drastically change the core item when upgrading
Try to enhance the name to reflect the new achievement
Always increase legendariness - it should be higher than before
Incorporate themes from the new task into tags and description, but preserve the core identity of the item
New Item Rules
When creating a new item:

Create a unique, descriptive core_id (e.g., "scepter_of_justice", "chronicle_of_bounces")
Set upgrades_previous to null
Keep legendariness modest (<40) unless the action is exceptional
Legendariness Guidelines
First-time items: <40 (unless truly exceptional)
Minor upgrades: +3 to +10
Significant milestones: +10 to +20
Major achievements: +20+
Never decrease legendariness when upgrading
Style Guidelines
Avoid sparkle ✨ and overuse of 🧭
Use distinctive, imaginative emojis
Be somewhat fantastical in naming
Keep names concise and evocative
Keep descriptions short (1-2 sentences max)
Output Format
Return ONLY valid JSON matching the provided structure. No prose, no explanation, no markdown fences.

